Adult female from Biliton (
Fig. 16B
)– colouration as for male, but subdued. Sides of body with single distinct reddish-pink stripe. All fins hyaline.

Adult male from Anjungan (
Fig. 16E
) – head dark brown on dorsum and sides, ventrum cream. Upper jaw yellowish brown with corresponding portion of lower jaw reddish; dorsal surface of exposed lower jaw brown, middle section of dermal flange on lower jaw with distinct pale blue and red markings; ventrum of lower jaw flange with distinct black margin from tip to region directly below upper jaw. Eye with upper half of iris pale blue. Operculum with scattering of melanophores, and pinkish on posterior part. Body with brown dorsal stripe, dorsum and sides pale brown, ventrum cream; sides with two distinct reddish-pink stripes from post-opercle to caudal-fin base, and a third faint pinkish stripe below the two stripes. Dorsal fin yellowish. Caudal fin yellowish. Anal, pelvic and pectoral fins hyaline.
